<subSubSection id="FB2CF78C92E47B2AABE1904ABEF0E751" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="2B758C844D46F2E613AE5082060DD25D" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="340F156DBF9849C3318E164811EDB82C" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
This species is named in reference to the type locality. It is used as an adjective for a place, with the Latin suffix - 
<emphasis id="405D12368728E5EE2CFC7A8F6531BE1D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">ensis</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A5317D78BB64CD7432D3ADB299F8BA00" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="6036CE6CC9056AA46A619C28C65FBB68" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FEB0B2FF94640E6431D9ABFC0C77E8AD" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Surface of the shell mostly smooth. Posterior infold of the carapace with a broad shelf. Dorsal margin rounded in both female and male. Posterior end clearly wider than anterior. Lateral eye well developed with black pigmented ommatidia. A1 8-segmented without d-bristle on the 8th joint. Uropodal lamellae with nine claws.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F443889E0E99E9A83513A94368639156" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph id="00C7139389367274ABAA450EB38F06FC" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6273561AFCAA8C19CDE9BF88003424F7" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="37D3B16A259F55885A25F347E49E6E4B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Female.</emphasis>
Shell (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A355AC76D5F033FBD65BFD0009D850BC" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Light microscopy and scanning electron microscopy images of Parasterope busanensis sp. nov. a-f holotype female adult: a External view b Lateral view from left valve c Spines on dorsal margin d Internal view of anterior part e L 5 ventral section f Internal view of posterior part g, h paratype male adult: g External view h Lateral view from right valve i Internal view of left valve." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672090" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">2a-f</figureCitation>
) Carapace oval, broadening at posterior, greatest height near middle, carapace length 1.25 mm, height 0.94 mm. Nine small horn-like spines near dorsal margin. Posterior infold between broad list and valve margin without setae.
</paragraph>
<caption id="78A731D2BB45989160689DDA54C7AB18" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672090" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" start="Figure 2" startId="F2">
<paragraph id="F872D51615F48B46144F281955C56AF2" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="ECCFA397EA490F4DAE1192301B6CBA5F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Figure 2.</emphasis>
Light microscopy and scanning electron microscopy images of 
<taxonomicName id="C40DA5C0426468D97851863656CFFFDF" authorityName="Pham &amp; Karanovic" authorityYear="2022" class="Ostracoda" family="Cylindroleberididae" genus="Parasterope" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Parasterope busanensis" order="Myodocopida" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="busanensis">
<emphasis id="B59667F590116BAA06634E3EB4D77151" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Parasterope busanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. 
<emphasis id="FEFD5E3843058FD3C710BDB3C69DDEED" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">a-f</emphasis>
holotype female adult: 
<emphasis id="C414D8F938911996FE46AB2B6A38DB5B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">a</emphasis>
