Lateral view from right valve 
<emphasis id="848DBA2248278C29F56C381961871473" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">i</emphasis>
Internal view of left valve.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="850B6421A961EFBD737EF53D423EB576" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
A1 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="FE359D2106951261DEC756FC19D5025D" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Parasterope busanensis sp. nov. holotype female adult: a A 1 b Bellonci organ c A 2 d Md e Mxl f L 5 g L 7 h F. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672091" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">3a</figureCitation>
). 1st joint: with no hair on broad surface; longer than 2nd joint. 2nd joint: one spinous dorsal seta, one short lateral bristle, and three proximal dorsal spines. 3rd joint: seven setae (one short ventral and six dorsal). 4th joint: three bristles (one long dorsal and two short ventral bristles) and two small ventral spines at mid length. 5th joint: sensory bristle with six filaments without short proximal terminal. 6th joint: one medial seta, attached to bottom of 7th joint boundary. 7th joint: a-bristle claw-like, bare; b-seta with marginal filaments; c-seta with marginal filaments. 8th joint: d-bristle absent; e-bristle with blunt tip; f- and g-bristles with marginal filaments.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DCCE4EA6F193AF8B2663EE31DEEE63D0" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672091" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" start="Figure 3" startId="F3">
<paragraph id="1D0D8FCECC2E9450482A13DDD336F372" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="6AFC2936C85FF560F93EDE7E0BD82E43" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Figure 3.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="D1CEB8B8C73DA5F540BEAD0AD00D8589" authorityName="Pham &amp; Karanovic" authorityYear="2022" class="Ostracoda" family="Cylindroleberididae" genus="Parasterope" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Parasterope busanensis" order="Myodocopida" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="busanensis">
<emphasis id="6A343467D7CCAB376966CEC356E91130" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Parasterope busanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. holotype female adult: 
<emphasis id="51C356538CE713EDE2DDAD7E4D2022E0" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">a</emphasis>
A1 
<emphasis id="EE94066C57843973DC05E31FB8D59A7A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">b</emphasis>
Bellonci organ 
<emphasis id="04F2DDB4BF8DB5DE8297327D559C888E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">c</emphasis>
A2 
<emphasis id="87834290480B67CDCA8C2CB5E3707356" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">d</emphasis>
Md 
<emphasis id="C9BC8E4BB505707578E4644C85373802" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">e</emphasis>
Mxl 
<emphasis id="BBF1B752C20FC51773C9696F5234619C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">f</emphasis>
L5 
<emphasis id="E38CE341F4922C0B6DCB140EF157F598" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">g</emphasis>
L7 
<emphasis id="A3CEE82987172D5906C9FEC57EC9929C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">h</emphasis>
F. Scale bar: 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="B9FC9591032CD1FE6F76BADDD8770542" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
Bellonci organ (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A5E1572A7FAA8850968B52CA928565E8" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Parasterope busanensis sp. nov. holotype female adult: a A 1 b Bellonci organ c A 2 d Md e Mxl f L 5 g L 7 h F. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672091" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">3b</figureCitation>
). Elongate with rounded tip, constriction at mid-point.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="15F36434A17E272AE92225F440D969CF" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="549C37FF6D3DD4C4B9BD05BC773AD11A" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Eyes</emphasis>
. Lateral eye with many ommatidia obscured by black pigment; 13 ommatidia visible. Medial eye rounded and unpigmented.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5F0D0E2E46F3015CDCE2F82FFB097443" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
A2. Protopodite: rounded without medial bristle. Endopodite (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="61BD8022D2E534E3C2AE2B12E3DABB46" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Parasterope busanensis sp. nov. holotype female adult: a A 1 b Bellonci organ c A 2 d Md e Mxl f L 5 g L 7 h F. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672091" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">3c</figureCitation>
): 2-jointed with long terminal bristle. Exopodite: 9-jointed; bristle of 2nd segment with spinules along ventral margin and spines along dorsal margin reaching 8th joint; 3rd-8th joints with natatory hairs and spines along proximal part of ventral margin. 9th article: four bristles (two long natatory and two short bristles). Articles 1-8 with minute spines at inner terminal corner.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E6F7B3BD7A1AD7DFA7DE6AC9D03AF417" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
Md (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="08E1E4812D02F69A294B04C0B71D4679" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Parasterope busanensis sp. nov. holotype female adult: a A 1 b Bellonci organ c A 2 d Md e Mxl f L 5 g L 7 h F. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672091" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">3d</figureCitation>
). Coxale endite ventral branch with spines forming four oblique rows. Basale endite with four spinous end bristles, three triaenid bristles with three or four pairs spines excluding terminal pair. Basale dorsal margin with two long terminal setae, without mid-bristle. Exopodite with hirsute tip and two small subterminal setae, exopodite almost same length as dorsal margin of first endopodite article. Endopodite: 1st joint: ventral margin with three bristles (one broken with short spines, one long with long marginal spines, and one shorter without spine or hair); 2nd joint: ventral margin: with three terminal bristles; dorsal margin: with stout a-, b-, c-, and d-bristles and one short bristle proximal to a-bristle; one long e-bristle and three medial bristles forming an oblique row between b- and c-bristles and adjacent to b-bristle; four medial bristles forming an oblique row adjacent to c-bristle; and one short bristle adjacent to d-bristle; f-bristle between c- and d-bristles, long, bare; g-bristle longer than f-bristle. End segment with a strong dorsal claw-like bristle without marginal spines, three juxtaposed stout bristles of equal length, and two thin bristles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CD0E8522876B7FEE17DFC48D72196EC9" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
Mxl (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="70E6AA80CDA9708A817C21E998DF121E" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Parasterope busanensis sp. nov. holotype female adult: a A 1 b Bellonci organ c A 2 d Md e Mxl f L 5 g L 7 h F. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672091" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">3e</figureCitation>
). Endite I with three bristles. Endite II with three bristles. Basale: one bare proximal ventral bristle at the middle and four short distal ventral bristles. Endopodite: 1st article absent 
<normalizedToken id="DF2DEB26CF07ECBCB02D5ACF5BE6ACC3" originalValue="α-seta">α-seta</normalizedToken>
and one hairy 
<normalizedToken id="36EA1E08ECC309962DE653F31F3AB866" originalValue="β-seta">β-seta</normalizedToken>
; 2nd article with two terminal bristles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C456AF8BB6165E2C2EAFCCC437D12097" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
L5 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="905F69A9A789550C6D0F8E97C167F09A" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Parasterope busanensis sp. nov. holotype female adult: a A 1 b Bellonci organ c A 2 d Md e Mxl f L 5 g L 7 h F. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672091" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">3f</figureCitation>
). Ventral section with fan of long setae. Comb: spinous exopodite bristle over past distal end of comb, two short bristles (ventral to base of exopodite bristle) with bases almost on ventral edge of comb, four bristles just proximal at the ventral edge of comb, without bristle to base of exopodite bristle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3DABDE77D58854DD586C65751E568D16" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">L6. Unknown</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AD54ECF92B4F3E05373312998CAA2817" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
L7 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7C64C5A746FBAAFFE89E136B1248C222" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Parasterope busanensis sp. nov. holotype female adult: a A 1 b Bellonci organ c A 2 d Md e Mxl f L 5 g L 7 h F. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672091" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">3g</figureCitation>
). Each limb with 12 bristles. Six proximal and six distal bristles (three on each side).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B8DA5DD2DE720514D5A3212EA38ADE3D" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
F (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6522445FC7C91ECA4FB3E0DBC2DF8992" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Parasterope busanensis sp. nov. holotype female adult: a A 1 b Bellonci organ c A 2 d Md e Mxl f L 5 g L 7 h F. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672091" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">3h</figureCitation>
). Each lamella with six claws and three posterior claws bristle-like. A total of nine claws and bristles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="05565ECC874FC1B7CAB761D94AAD1513" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="D7BF1EFEB581E8AFE9E6679646DD9E90" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Male.</emphasis>
All features are comparable to adult female; important differences are listed below.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="485AB353C77CD25DE9573F353FCAEE1B" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
Shell (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A5638BE9C4C4B3C9887C0FCD1C803BB7" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Light microscopy and scanning electron microscopy images of Parasterope busanensis sp. nov. a-f holotype female adult: a External view b Lateral view from left valve c Spines on dorsal margin d Internal view of anterior part e L 5 ventral section f Internal view of posterior part g, h paratype male adult: g External view h Lateral view from right valve i Internal view of left valve." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672090" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">2g-i</figureCitation>
). Carapace more elongate than that of female and with more open incisure, hairs forming vertical row near posterior end, carapace length 1.36 mm, height at middle 0.9 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="192C51203D68956E3BCF28F0CE7F28A3" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
A1 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="73BB10C863E2D0BC1673D0754D7796D2" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Parasterope busanensis sp. nov. paratype male adult: a A 1 b A 2 c Md d Bellonci organ. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672092" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">4a</figureCitation>
). Sensory seta with robust stem and many filaments. 7th and 8th joints with very long c- and f- setae (long as carapace length) each with numerous of marginal filaments. 2nd and 4th joints without dorsal margin spines.
</paragraph>
<caption id="1E556D1C423D2811F98EFE2EBFE31F5F" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672092" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" start="Figure 4" startId="F4">
<paragraph id="5CF3F87D8639B74C8E8D75C905A91043" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="5183B064B8F13A455FC012B136475094" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Figure 4.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="27CEC37233DA9D7234DA6BF024D5631E" authorityName="Pham &amp; Karanovic" authorityYear="2022" class="Ostracoda" family="Cylindroleberididae" genus="Parasterope" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Parasterope busanensis" order="Myodocopida" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="busanensis">
<emphasis id="67238F22B56FB0FB10C4F5CCFD5394BC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Parasterope busanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. paratype male adult: 
<emphasis id="6FFEF4A4671D4DBE41CC87279CBA25D1" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">a</emphasis>
A1 
<emphasis id="51211303F8039AEC37253712211C9D80" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">b</emphasis>
A2 
<emphasis id="D04CAF0772FB28E55908C8442A2C4734" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">c</emphasis>
Md 
<emphasis id="A2A52AF0CE9356E1FB9EA20A6CF4EE1A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">d</emphasis>
Bellonci organ. Scale bar: 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="2A4C9F02991C210079D2C819B1B2430B" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
A2 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="853A2485F29E2CD3F6CE7470475B45AE" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Parasterope busanensis sp. nov. paratype male adult: a A 1 b A 2 c Md d Bellonci organ. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672092" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">4b</figureCitation>
). Endopodite with 3-jointed, article two with two lateral setae, article three recurved with 1 proximal seta.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8F440D8AC342E67154789D6D2F897087" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
Md (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="FF8A799A4533ACB489517FC73912A73B" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Parasterope busanensis sp. nov. paratype male adult: a A 1 b A 2 c Md d Bellonci organ. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672092" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">4c</figureCitation>
). Basale dorsal margin with one seta at mid-length. Endopodite: two relatively long bristles proximal to a-bristle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CFCFE0A00964768EAA57C17413AFC5A3" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="AA7D3EB076ADEEA72FCDA7A483763569" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Eyes</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9529D1AECFF79E96BDB14D6BAF7FA3E9" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Parasterope busanensis sp. nov. paratype male adult: a A 1 b A 2 c Md d Bellonci organ. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672092" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">4d</figureCitation>
). Lateral eye with more than 17 ommatidia. Medial eye rounded and unpigmented.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="00C4C72DFF4AE53238F79783BE4808E2" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="4065F17416174EB405D65E171742EAF8" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Reproductive organs</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E2FB1B3DA0FAB5F53209AF2412F73222" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Parasterope busanensis sp. nov. paratype male adult: a A 1 b A 2 c Md d Bellonci organ. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672092" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">4f</figureCitation>
). Copulatory limbs are coalesced proximally, in generally, shorter than the furca lamella. The lobe is distally subdivided into three small lobes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="15AE37406814A4DB6B488545E4E238E3" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="67874AD8FE82BF7F4A76977CB2802732" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D3C065D6FB3916FB1911678AEE176609" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
The new species is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="7A12DCF0A48641C86BBFFCA6C76CCE60" genus="P." lsidName="P. iota" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="iota">
<emphasis id="D4F37AB7BADE9009ADF4F1882C783659" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. iota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kornicker, Harrison-Nelson &amp; Coles, 2007, described from Kapua Channel (
<normalizedToken id="3D920562273FFE2387038B5049E94CA1" originalValue="Waikïkï">Waikiki</normalizedToken>
, Hawaii). The first joint of the A1 of 
<taxonomicName id="903A716D87762CB367926BBAC809B780" genus="P." lsidName="P. busanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="busanensis">
<emphasis id="3904254C371B7AC532FD898C64B16CFE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. busanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is without hair on the broad surface, present in 
<taxonomicName id="9DFAD59B0562A7FB459726F441C5AD9B" genus="P." lsidName="P. iota" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="iota">
<emphasis id="1D9E6A3D1D4ECEBA813E19817E74390D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. iota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In addition, the 3rd-8th joints of 
<taxonomicName id="426F81AE14FA91CC762AF866A0483805" genus="P." lsidName="P. iota" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="iota">
<emphasis id="9932713E4B90860995087B0E722C7F92" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. iota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
each have fairly stout proximal ventral spines, absent in 
<taxonomicName id="F4C1C9BF40BA8B4B5C0ED3F43884DBDD" genus="P." lsidName="P. busanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="busanensis">
<emphasis id="7AB82DCBEFC790459D7E4E26EA4A1039" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. busanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The distal margin of the Mxl of 
<taxonomicName id="0BE7776C6976FCBDCE4B3092626DF8D1" genus="P." lsidName="P. busanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="busanensis">
<emphasis id="6329078411F66363EC3E8D07E0BC1AD2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. busanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bears four bristles compared to two in 
<taxonomicName id="CF67386D39F276B63317867F53A7D2EC" genus="P." lsidName="P. iota" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="iota">
<emphasis id="C809B786AF8F49A15DFEA531DD5831E0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. iota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and three bristles (one minute) near the ventral margin rather than five in 
<taxonomicName id="111B6232CB6CF03FB3AF727D3B36495C" genus="P." lsidName="P. iota" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="iota">
<emphasis id="5EE3DAC5E7C7EC6FBC2F956255565A21" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. iota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The new species shares many characters with 
<taxonomicName id="CFEE8A79FB3662020944FE091E36BA41" genus="P." lsidName="P. gamurru" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="gamurru">
<emphasis id="71CEB96AB8E89C5F97A2908DABBEA716" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. gamurru</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Syme &amp; Poore, 2006 described from Queensland, Australia (
<bibRefCitation id="9CEEC326CEA0D6061C25A5D652D8E490" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.1305.1.5" author="Syme, AE" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" pagination="51 - 67" refId="B39" refString="Syme, AE, Poore, GCB, 2006a. Three new ostracod species from coastal Australian waters (Crustacea: Ostracoda: Myodocopa: Cylindroleberididae). Zootaxa 1305 (1): 51 - 67, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.1305.1.5" title="Three new ostracod species from coastal Australian waters (Crustacea: Ostracoda: Myodocopa: Cylindroleberididae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.1305.1.5" volume="1305" year="2006 a">Syme and Poore 2006a</bibRefCitation>
), but lacks the nodes on the dorsal margin of the 5th joint on the A1, which is a prominent character of 
<taxonomicName id="CCF007636DF23D8044B0F3FE0847640F" genus="P." lsidName="P. gamurru" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="gamurru">
<emphasis id="63A274ECF1433E7162D48C9AF5899373" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. gamurru</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The new species also bears two oblique rows of cleaning setae on the medial side of the Md 2nd joint, compared to only one in 
<taxonomicName id="569FA18E54E72ABF6B3C5450891AB1F1" genus="P." lsidName="P. gamurru" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="gamurru">
<emphasis id="B193D5B857BB46F6E40EEDD78C89104F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. gamurru</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The endite II of 
<taxonomicName id="8E7373DDFB2893FE71AA7CE70BDA1FA6" genus="P." lsidName="P. busanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="busanensis">
<emphasis id="EA736928C38D3E143D3714D3A0BBA47D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. busanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from that of 
<taxonomicName id="FB122FE06C7EDE533AD40196BF0BD7E0" genus="P." lsidName="P. pacifica" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="pacifica">
<emphasis id="5112E040CDFEF69BDC0BF445C28293BF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. pacifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kornicker and Harrison-Nelson, 2005 from Johnston Atoll (
<bibRefCitation id="8A1F22545F413FCB359CFFC576CD36B7" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1353/psc.2005.0038" author="Kornicker, LS" journalOrPublisher="Pacific Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" pagination="323 - 362" refId="B21" refString="Kornicker, LS, Harrison-Nelson, E, 2005. Ostracoda from Johnston Atoll, Pacific Ocean, and proposal of a new tribe, Bruuniellini (Myodocopina: Cylindroleberididae). Pacific Science 59 (3): 323 - 362, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1353/psc.2005.0038" title="Ostracoda from Johnston Atoll, Pacific Ocean, and proposal of a new tribe, Bruuniellini (Myodocopina: Cylindroleberididae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1353/psc.2005.0038" volume="59" year="2005">Kornicker and Harrison-Nelson 2005</bibRefCitation>
) in having three rather than four bristles. The 3rd joint of the Md in 
<taxonomicName id="51A023044B4C4CF77326667C94132143" genus="P." lsidName="P. theta" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="theta">
<emphasis id="855566259CEA6BD78E4BEC2257538170" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. theta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kornicker, Harrison-Nelson &amp; Coles, 2007 from 
<normalizedToken id="2BB78008D6C1E2050FF0AE75FBE55297" originalValue="Waikïkï">Waikiki</normalizedToken>
, Hawaii (
<bibRefCitation id="674D161784752011B57C2FC2D66C604D" author="Kornicker, LS" journalOrPublisher="Bishop Museum bulletin in Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" pagination="1 - 128" refId="B23" refString="Kornicker, LS, Harrison-Nelson, E, Coles, SL, 2007. Ostracoda (Myodocopina) from O'ahu and French Frigate Shoals, Hawaiian Islands. Bishop Museum bulletin in Zoology 8: 1 - 128" title="Ostracoda (Myodocopina) from O'ahu and French Frigate Shoals, Hawaiian Islands." volume="8" year="2007">Kornicker et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
). The same character is present in 
<taxonomicName id="30AA7AAE9E93552AA6265A3AD8EDB6DE" genus="P." lsidName="P. sigma" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="sigma">
<emphasis id="93B1C9915B504E475F463D4335A33F23" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. sigma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kornicker, Harrison-Nelson &amp; Coles, 2007 from 
<normalizedToken id="6C0CE9D6CDBFD397074159225514B0A1" originalValue="Käneohe">Kaeneohe</normalizedToken>
Bay, Hawaii (
<bibRefCitation id="4D2C681878E60256A6E6BD4D652767A5" author="Kornicker, LS" journalOrPublisher="Bishop Museum bulletin in Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" pagination="1 - 128" refId="B23" refString="Kornicker, LS, Harrison-Nelson, E, Coles, SL, 2007. Ostracoda (Myodocopina) from O'ahu and French Frigate Shoals, Hawaiian Islands. Bishop Museum bulletin in Zoology 8: 1 - 128" title="Ostracoda (Myodocopina) from O'ahu and French Frigate Shoals, Hawaiian Islands." volume="8" year="2007">Kornicker et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
), and 
<taxonomicName id="D58B90456799EDF76F30E158682B95FF" genus="P." lsidName="P. zeta" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="zeta">
<emphasis id="F84B8B262E5183D66988DF77342DD5FD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. zeta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kornicker, 1986 from the Gulf of Mexico (
<bibRefCitation id="721A701862E641B72E571E06CF2A69F6" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.425" author="Kornicker, LS" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" pagination="1 - 139" refId="B18" refString="Kornicker, LS, 1986. Cylindroleberididae of the Western North Atlantic and the Northern Gulf of Mexico, and Zoogeography of the Myodocopina (Ostracoda). Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology 425: 1 - 139, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.425" title="Cylindroleberididae of the Western North Atlantic and the Northern Gulf of Mexico, and Zoogeography of the Myodocopina (Ostracoda)." url="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.425" volume="425" year="1986">Kornicker 1986</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4BF4D61B3A58ECF86B3BF558866E5F60" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
The sexual dimorphism found in the new species, the morphology of the dorsal mid-bristle on the basale of Md, and the number of bristles proximal to the a-bristle on the endopodite of the Md, have never been described in 
<taxonomicName id="477E5F8279F7EDEC1C003766555A8853" class="Ostracoda" family="Cylindroleberididae" genus="Parasterope" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Parasterope" order="Myodocopida" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="39A311DB96FB2688BB4A43BD40113B56" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Parasterope</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E5B5D07554930B52C973CD5E859E8676" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">GenBank numbers 16S: OK048681, OK048682; 18S: OK048719, OK048720.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
